<br>
Axis and collision problems are clearly giving SoE fits.<br>
<br>
The problem is a very archaiac way for mobs to navigate that hasn't been givin much thought. It has been noted by players time and time again, and it looks that SoE has finally tried to/been forced to fix this long long long standing problem. Instead of walking around an object, mobs usually warp over or through them. With the recent changes in the axis, collision, and movement, mobs, which were never very bright to begin with, can not navigate around objects. Without being able to walk through, or climb over stuff every roamer is just going under the world.<br>
<br>
Another long standing part of the problems, is mobs that spawn in bunches are now getting stuck together, and poofing. I watched this happen several times in EC with spiderlings, orc pawns, and skeletons.<br>
<br>
Sadly, they should have never gone live with the DX9 patch, and have done nothing but passed along a bunch of problems to the live servers. This is causing a lot of frustration, and probably losing them business.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of fun things going on with the anniversery, the quests, the skeleton invasions, and the fabled mobs. That is all getting overshadowed with the patches during the last couple of weeks. People are logging off in frustration, Raids are getting interrupted, and cancelled.<br>
<br>
SoE really needs to start listening to their player base, and quit passing off patches just to meet a dead line. Hint: Test it, when you think it is working properly, test it again, listen to the testers, and fix the problems. Think you have it right? TEST IT AGAIN! <br>
<br>
This patch envolving the DX9 and mob pathing updates should never have made it past the test server. <p>Mercuria Cestlavie <br>
